    "summary": "Vicki de Klerk-Rubin is the Executive Director of the Validation Training Institute (VTI). Over the past 38 years, VTI has built an international network of partnerships including 14 Authorized Validation Organizations in 14 countries, 8,214 Validation workers, 860 group practitioners, 449 Validation teachers and 17 Validation Masters. \n\nMs. de Klerk has been teaching Validation (including different methods of \u2018centering\u2019 which is a critical element in practicing Validation since 1989. She has given Validation workshops, lectures and training programs in Australia, Austria, Belgium, China, Denmark, England, Finland, France, Great Britain, Germany, Ireland, Israel, Italy, Japan, Jordan, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Spain, Sweden and the United States. She is a Dutch-trained registered nurse (HBO-V, 1997), has an MBA from Fordham University (1983) and a BFA from Boston University (1978). \n\nShe has been a Master Validation Teacher since 2002, the highest level of certification given from VTI. Together, with her mother, Naomi Feil, she revised the books, \u201cValidation: the Feil Method\u201d and \u201cThe Validation Breakthrough.\u201d She is the author of \u201cValidation Techniques for Dementia Care: the Family Guide to Improving Communication\u201d and the work book: \u201cCommunicate with Older Adults with Cognitive Decline: Validation for First Responders.\u201d ",
